title: Following Glenn Rosewall out of the outfit formerly known as BBY
text:
Former BBY boss Glenn Rosewall's Bellevue Hill penthouse is still to be snapped up. David Rowe Share on twitter Share on Google Plus by Will Glasgow AIMS Financial Group's George Wang took over what remained of Glenn Rosewall 's stockbroking business BBY a little less than two months ago.
The outfit was promptly rebranded Asia Pacific Prudential Group, with talk of expansion into China.
Behind the headlines, some of the old staff have been heading for the door.
It wasn't a great surprise to hear that among those to leave was Jane Quinn . The office manager was very much a Rosewall loyalist.
And what of Glenn's penthouse in Sydney's eastern suburbs that we noted a few weeks ago was on the market?
LJ Hooker Double Bay agent Alain Waitsman says it's still to be snapped up. It remains scheduled for an August 1 auction.
BBY's unhappy creditors will be watching with some interest.
